The paper deals with communication complexity of functions, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The use of quantum communication and the comparison with classical communication suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The mention of SMP (Simultaneous Message Passing) and the analysis of the communication complexity of a functional problem suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The mention of an efficient solution for a function in the weakest commonly studied regime of quantum communication suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories.
